conditions.message:
Memcached can be accessed via port 11211 on the following DNS name from within your cluster:
memcached-sample00.memcached-operator-system.svc.cluster.local

If you'd like to test your instance, forward the port locally:

  export POD_NAME=$(kubectl get pods --namespace memcached-operator-system -l "app.kubernetes.io/name=memcached,app.kubernetes.io/instance=memcached-sample00" -o jsonpath="{.items[0].metadata.name}")
  kubectl port-forward $POD_NAME 11211

In another tab, attempt to set a key:

  $ echo -e 'set mykey 0 60 5\r\nhello\r' | nc localhost 11211

You should see:

  STORED

deployedRelease.manifest:
---
# Source: memcached/templates/svc.yaml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: memcached-sample00
  namespace: memcached-operator-system
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: memcached
    helm.sh/chart: memcached-0.0.1
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: memcached-sample00
    app.kubernetes.io/version: "1.5.20"
    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: Helm
  annotations:
    {}
spec:
  clusterIP: None
  ports:
  - name: memcache
    port: 11211
    targetPort: memcache
  selector:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: memcached
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: memcached-sample00
---
# Source: memcached/templates/statefulset.yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: StatefulSet
metadata:
  name: memcached-sample00
  namespace: memcached-operator-system
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: memcached
    helm.sh/chart: memcached-0.0.1
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: memcached-sample00
    app.kubernetes.io/version: "1.5.20"
    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: Helm
spec:
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app.kubernetes.io/name: memcached
      app.kubernetes.io/instance: memcached-sample00
  serviceName: memcached-sample00
  replicas: 1
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app.kubernetes.io/name: memcached
        app.kubernetes.io/instance: memcached-sample00
    spec:
      affinity:
        podAntiAffinity:
          preferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
          - weight: 5
            podAffinityTerm:
              topologyKey: "kubernetes.io/hostname"
              labelSelector:
                matchLabels:
                  app.kubernetes.io/name: memcached
                  app.kubernetes.io/instance: memcached-sample00
      containers:
      - name: memcached-sample00
        image: memcached:1.5.20
        imagePullPolicy: ""
        command:
        - memcached
        - -m 64
        - -o
        - modern
        - -v
        ports:
        - name: memcache
          containerPort: 11211
        livenessProbe:
          tcpSocket:
            port: memcache
          initialDelaySeconds: 30
          timeoutSeconds: 5
        readinessProbe:
          tcpSocket:
            port: memcache
          initialDelaySeconds: 5
          timeoutSeconds: 1
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 64Mi
  updateStrategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
deployedRelease.name: memcached-sample00

apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: memcached-sample08
  namespace: memcached-operator-system
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: memcached
    helm.sh/chart: memcached-0.0.1
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: memcached-sample08
    app.kubernetes.io/version: "1.5.20"
    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: Helm
  annotations:
    {}
spec:
  clusterIP: None
  ports:
  - name: memcache
    port: 11211
    targetPort: memcache
  selector:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: memcached
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: memcached-sample08
---
# Source: memcached/templates/statefulset.yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: StatefulSet
metadata:
  name: memcached-sample08
  namespace: memcached-operator-system
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/name: memcached
    helm.sh/chart: memcached-0.0.1
    app.kubernetes.io/instance: memcached-sample08
    app.kubernetes.io/version: "1.5.20"
    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: Helm
spec:
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app.kubernetes.io/name: memcached
      app.kubernetes.io/instance: memcached-sample08
  serviceName: memcached-sample08
  replicas: 1
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app.kubernetes.io/name: memcached
        app.kubernetes.io/instance: memcached-sample08
    spec:
      affinity:
        podAntiAffinity:
          preferredDuringSchedulingIgnoredDuringExecution:
          - weight: 5
            podAffinityTerm:
              topologyKey: "kubernetes.io/hostname"
              labelSelector:
                matchLabels:
                  app.kubernetes.io/name: memcached
                  app.kubernetes.io/instance: memcached-sample08
      containers:
      - name: memcached-sample08
        image: memcached:1.5.20
        imagePullPolicy: ""
        command:
        - memcached
        - -m 64
        - -o
        - modern
        - -v
        ports:
        - name: memcache
          containerPort: 11211
        livenessProbe:
          tcpSocket:
            port: memcache
          initialDelaySeconds: 30
          timeoutSeconds: 5
        readinessProbe:
          tcpSocket:
            port: memcache
          initialDelaySeconds: 5
          timeoutSeconds: 1
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: 50m
            memory: 64Mi
  updateStrategy:
    type: RollingUpdate
deployedRelease.name: memcached-sample08

conditions.message:
Memcached can be accessed via port 11211 on the following DNS name from within your cluster:
memcached-sample09.memcached-operator-system.svc.cluster.local

If you'd like to test your instance, forward the port locally:

  export POD_NAME=$(kubectl get pods --namespace memcached-operator-system -l "app.kubernetes.io/name=memcached,app.kubernetes.io/instance=memcached-sample09" -o jsonpath="{.items[0].metadata.name}")
  kubectl port-forward $POD_NAME 11211

In another tab, attempt to set a key:

  $ echo -e 'set mykey 0 60 5\r\nhello\r' | nc localhost 11211
